✅ RENDER BACKGROUND WORKER SETTINGS

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
RECOMMENDED: Deploy via render.yaml (IaC)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Connect your repo to Render. render.yaml in the repo root auto-configures
the worker service — no manual dashboard settings needed except env vars.
Then set the env vars marked sync:false in the Render dashboard.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
MANUAL DASHBOARD SETTINGS (if not using render.yaml)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

🐳 Deployment
  Runtime: Docker
  Dockerfile Path: ./Dockerfile         ← build from repo, NOT from Docker Hub image
  Docker Context: . (root of repo)

  ⚠️  CRITICAL: Leave "Docker Command" BLANK
      The Dockerfile CMD is: python3 -u main.py
      If you override it with "bash -c while true; do sleep 60; done"
      the worker will never process any jobs.

🏷 Name
  reels-video-processor

🌍 Region
  Oregon (US West)

💻 Instance Type
  Starter ($7/month) — 512 MB RAM, 0.5 CPU
  ⚠️  FFmpeg Ken Burns rendering is CPU-intensive.
      If jobs are slow, upgrade to Standard (1 CPU).

💾 Disk
  Mount path: /tmp/reels
  Size: 5 GB

🔐 Environment Variables (set in dashboard)
  REDIS_URL=redis://default:password@host:6379
  DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host:5432/dbname
  N8N_CALLBACK_URL=https://reel-video.app.n8n.cloud/webhook/render-callback
  B2_ENDPOINT=https://s3.us-west-000.backblazeb2.com
  B2_APPLICATION_KEY_ID=your_key_id
  B2_APPLICATION_KEY=your_application_key
  B2_BUCKET_NAME=your_bucket_name
  ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=your_elevenlabs_key
  REPLICATE_API_TOKEN=your_replicate_token
  TEMP_DIR=/tmp/reels

⚙️  Pre-Deploy Command
  (leave empty)
